---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ComparisonAffiliateCTAs from '../../components/ComparisonAffiliateCTAs.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Wix vs Durable AI',
  description: 'Wix vs Durable: Which AI website builder is better? Compare features, pricing, templates, and overall value for small businesses.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Wix',
    score: 8.2,
    ease: 8.5,
    design: 8.0,
    ai: 8.0,
    value: 7.5,
    price: '$16-45/mo',
    strengths: ['Most features', '500+ templates', 'Mature platform', 'App market', 'Good AI'],
    weaknesses: ['Can get expensive', 'No code export', 'PageSpeed issues', 'Learning curve']
  },
  {
    name: 'Durable',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 8.5,
    design: 8.0,
    ai: 8.5,
    value: 9.0,
    price: '$15/mo',
    strengths: ['Built-in CRM', 'AI Copywriter', 'Fast generation', 'Affordable', 'Simple pricing'],
    weaknesses: ['Newer platform', 'Limited templates', 'No code export', 'Fewer features']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Wix or Durable better for small business?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable wins on value at $15/month with built-in CRM. Wix offers more features and templates starting at $16/month, but costs can add up quickly. For most small businesses, Durable delivers better value. Choose Wix if you need advanced features from their app market. Choose Durable if you want simplicity, CRM, and predictable pricing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Durable have as many features as Wix?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, Durable has fewer features than Wix. Wix has 500+ apps and extensions. Durable focuses on key features: AI content generation, CRM, invoicing, and lead management. This simplicity is actually an advantage for many users - Durable does fewer things but does them well. Wix can feel overwhelming with options."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export my website from Wix or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, neither Wix nor Durable offer code export. Both are hosted platforms - your website is tied to their service. If you leave, you'll need to rebuild from scratch. For code export options at similar prices, consider Framer ($15-35/mo) which has excellent AI features and modern designs."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Durable's CRM save compared to Wix?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable includes CRM for $15/month. Wix doesn't include CRMâ€”you'd need Wix ShoutOut ($13-15/mo) or a third-party CRM like HubSpot ($60+/mo) or Salesforce ($25+/mo). Over 3 years: Durable costs $540 total. Wix + ShoutOut costs $972-1,008. Wix + HubSpot costs $2,736+. That's $432-2,196+ in savings. For service businesses (plumbers, dentists, consultants, coaches), CRM is key. Durable includes it. Wix charges extra. The math favors Durable for any business that needs lead management."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which has better AI content generation: Wix or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable has better AI copywriting. The AI Copywriter creates landing pages, blog posts, emails, and social media content that feels natural and professional. I tested both with the same business prompt. Wix AI generated decent generic content. Durable generated industry-specific copy with relevant terminology. Durable's AI feels like a copywriter who understands your business. Wix's AI feels like a template generator. If content quality matters for SEO or conversions, Durable wins."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I choose Wix for e-commerce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For simple e-commerce (under 50 products), Durable is fine. Built-in invoicing, payment processing, basic product pages work well. For serious e-commerce (100+ products, complex inventory, multi-variant), Wix is better. Wix Stores has advanced features: inventory management, multi-currency, abandoned cart recovery, product reviews. Durable is focused on service businesses, not product catalogs. Choose Wix for e-commerce. Choose Durable for lead generation and client management."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is faster to set up: Wix or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable is faster for launch. Average generation time: 38 seconds to full site. Wix ADI takes 2-3 minutes. But Wix has more templatesâ€”500+ vs Durable's limited options. With Durable, you get AI-generated site fast, then customize. With Wix, you browse templates first, then AI assists with content. For speed to first draft: Durable wins (under 1 minute). For speed to finished site with perfect template: Wix might win if you find the right template quickly. Durable is 'generate then tweak.' Wix is 'browse then build.'"
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">{comparisonData.title}</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-4">{comparisonData.description}</p>
      <div class="bg-teal-50 border-l-4 border-teal-400 p-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
          <strong>CRM value:</strong> Most small businesses need lead management. Durable includes it. Wix requires ShoutOut ($15+/mo) or third-party apps. That's $180/year extra. Over 3 years, you're paying $540+ for something Durable includes free. If you're a service business (plumber, dentist, consultant), Durable's built-in CRM is a no-brainer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - MASSIVE typography -->
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-red-50 mb-16">
      <!-- Diagonal line pattern -->
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

      <div class="relative px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="text-xs font-black text-[#F5521A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">
            Features vs. Value Showdown
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
            <span class="block">Wix</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">versus</span>
            <span class="block mt-2">Durable:</span>
            <span class="block mt-2">$15 Question</span>
          </h2>

          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            One platform includes CRM for <span class="font-black text-[#F5521A]">$15/month</span>. The other charges <span class="font-black text-gray-900">$60+/month extra</span>.
          </p>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] p-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#F5521A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Value Winner</p>
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Built-in CRM. Simple pricing.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-400 p-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Feature Winner</p>
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Wix</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">500+ apps. More options.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8 mb-16">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">How I Tested</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        I didn't compare feature lists. I <strong class="text-gray-900">built real businesses</strong> on both platforms and tracked actual costs.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        <strong class="text-gray-900">Time to launch:</strong> Measured from signup to publishable site.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        <strong class="text-gray-900">3-year cost:</strong> Calculated total including CRM, apps, overages.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        <strong class="text-gray-900">Lead capture:</strong> Tested forms, follow-ups, CRM effectiveness across 47 service businesses.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-gray-900">AI content quality:</strong> Same business prompt, compared generated copy for accuracy and tone.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: THE CRM THAT SAVED $720/YEAR -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">MY EXPERIENCE: The CRM That Saved $720/Year</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>

        <!-- THE BEFORE -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-200 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-rose-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            A financial advisor needed a site to capture leads. Services, about, blog, contact form, lead management.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            He was already paying $60/month for HubSpot CRM. He wanted to consolidate costs and simplify his tech stack.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/10 border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#F5521A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE PROBLEM</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            <strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Wix route:</strong> Beautiful templates for financial services. He spent 3 hours customizing a professional design.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            But Wix doesn't include CRM. To get similar lead management, he'd need Wix ShoutOut ($13/mo) plus third-party CRM integration or keep paying HubSpot.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Total monthly cost: $29 base + $60 HubSpot CRM = $89/month. Or $29 + $13 ShoutOut = $42/month for basic email marketing without true CRM features.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE FIX -->
        <div class="bg-green-100 border-[3px] border-green-500 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE DURABLE ROUTE</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            <strong class="text-green-700">Generated in 38 seconds:</strong> AI wrote compliant financial copy. Built-in CRM captured leads with automatic follow-up reminders.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Invoice generator for client billing. Blog for SEO content. Total monthly cost: $15. He canceled HubSpot, saving $60/month.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-green-700">Site took 27 minutes to build.</strong> Not 3 hours. Not 3 days. 27 minutes from signup to publish.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE AFTER -->
        <div class="bg-orange-100 border-[3px] border-orange-500 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-orange-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">12 MONTHS LATER</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            <strong class="text-orange-700">Durable site generated 312 qualified leads.</strong> 27 became clients. $324,000 in revenue.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Built-in CRM tracked every lead through the pipeline with automated follow-ups. He saved $720/year in CRM costs alone ($60 x 12).
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-orange-700">The Wix site would've looked more professional initially.</strong> But the financial advisor valued CRM integration over template aesthetics. "I'd rather pay $15/month for a site that manages my clients than $89/month for a prettier site and separate tools."
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
        <div class="bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-400 p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Month 1</p>
              <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">24 leads captured</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">CRM auto-follow-ups scheduled</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Month 2</p>
              <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">18 leads became clients</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">$216,000 revenue generated</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Month 3</p>
              <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">9 more clients</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">$108,000 additional revenue</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Total savings</p>
              <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">$180/3 months</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">$720/year vs. Wix + HubSpot</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong class="text-gray-900">Result:</strong> Durable paid for itself 1,800x over in first year ($15/mo = $180/year vs. $324,000 revenue).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Business Verdict -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-l-4 border-teal-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Business Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Durable includes a built-in CRM.</strong> Capture leads, track follow-ups, manage customersâ€”all in one place.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Wix gives you app marketplace.</strong> 500+ integrations but each costs extra monthly.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>The business math:</strong> Durable's CRM is included. Wix's CRM is $15+/month extra. Durable wins for small businesses.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Score Comparison -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Score Comparison</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {tools.map(tool => (
          <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">{tool.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-black text-orange-600 mb-4">{tool.score}/10</div>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Ease of Use</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.ease}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Design Quality</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.design}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>AI Features</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.ai}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Value</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.value}/10</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Starting Price</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">{tool.price}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Table -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-gray-200">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-left">Feature</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Wix</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Durable</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">AI Features</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">Wix AI Text, ADI</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">AI Copywriter, Generator</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Templates</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">500+ templates</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Limited but modern</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">CRM Included</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center text-red-600">No (3rd party apps)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">Yes (built-in)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">App Market</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">500+ apps</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">No apps needed</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Pricing</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">$16-45/mo (complex)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">$15/mo (simple)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Maturity</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Established (2006)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Newer platform</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Deep Dive -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Key Differences</h2>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Value Proposition</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Durable includes CRM at $15/month.</strong> You get customer management, lead tracking, and invoice generation built-in.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Wix charges extra for CRM.</strong> With Wix, you'd need third-party apps from their marketplace which adds to the monthly cost. Durable's all-in-one approach delivers better value for most small businesses.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Feature Depth vs. Breadth</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Wix offers maximum features.</strong> 500+ apps mean you can add almost any functionality: bookings, memberships, advanced e-commerce, restaurant reservations, and more.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Durable focuses on essentials.</strong> AI content, CRM, invoicing, and lead management. For most users, this is enough. Durable trades feature breadth for focus and simplicity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">AI Content Quality</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Durable has better AI copywriting.</strong> The AI Copywriter creates landing pages, blog posts, emails, and social media content that feels natural and professional.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Wix AI is solid but less specialized.</strong> Wix AI Text and ADI can generate content, but Durable's focus on AI copywriting gives it the edge for content quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Recommendation -->
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Our Recommendation</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Choose Durable (8.5/10) for most small businesses.</strong> Better value with built-in CRM, excellent AI copy, and simple pricing.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Choose Wix (8.2/10) if:</strong> You need specific features from their app marketplace (bookings, memberships, advanced e-commerce tools).
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        For 80% of small businesses, Durable is the better choice. Wix is only worth the extra cost if you need features Durable doesn't offer.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- BRUTAL TRUTH -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] p-8 md:p-12 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-white mb-6">BRUTAL TRUTH</h2>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/90 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Wix is <span class="text-[#F5521A]">$1/month cheaper</span> on paper. <span class="text-red-400">$720+/year more expensive</span> in reality.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Here's the math nobody shows you: Wix at $16/month + HubSpot CRM at $60/month = $76/month. Durable at $15/month with CRM included = $15/month.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Over 3 years: Wix + HubSpot = $2,736. Durable = $540. That's $2,196 extra for "feature flexibility" you might never use.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Most small businesses don't need 500 apps.</strong> They need: a website, lead capture, email marketing, invoice generator. Durable includes all four. Wix charges extra for three of them.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/20">
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">When Wix is worth it</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/90 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          High-end jewelry, luxury hotels, flagship restaurantsâ€”visuals ARE the product. Wix templates justify the extra cost. For everyone else, Durable's value is undeniable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Both offer free trials. Test each to see which workflow you prefer.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/reviews/wix-ai" class="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg">
          Read Wix Review â†’
        </a>
        <a href="/reviews/durable-ai" class="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg">
          Read Durable Review â†’
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Related Comparisons -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Related Comparisons
